{"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore\/visiblenode"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode\/drawVisible(_:_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VisibleNode","preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO"}],"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:e:s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO11ChromaShellE04drawC0ySS_AD8ConsumedVtSi_SitF","modules":[{"name":"ChromaShell","relatedModules":["ScribeCore"]}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Extended Enumeration","fragments":[{"text":"extension","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO","text":"VisibleNode","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"VisibleNode","symbolKind":"extension","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VisibleNode","kind":"identifier"}],"extendedModule":"ScribeCore"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell","doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore"]]},"references":{"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell/ScribeCore":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore","role":"collection","title":"ScribeCore","abstract":[]},"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell":{"url":"\/documentation\/chromashell","abstract":[{"text":"A package to add more Chroma to your Swift terminal life.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell","title":"ChromaShell","role":"collection"},"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell/ScribeCore/VisibleNode":{"type":"topic","title":"VisibleNode","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VisibleNode","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore\/visiblenode","fragments":[{"text":"extension","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO","text":"VisibleNode","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode","role":"symbol"},"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell/ScribeCore/VisibleNode/drawVisible(_:_:)":{"type":"topic","title":"drawVisible(_:_:)","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore\/visiblenode\/drawvisible(_:_:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"drawVisible","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> (","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11ChromaShell10ANSIStringa","text":"ANSIString","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11ChromaShell8ConsumedV","text":"Consumed","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A this point we can assume that all or most of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed to us Almost fit into the height and width we have provided. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"job of this function is to tile or materialize the nodes into ASCII","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"escape codes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The following assumptions are being made for now. This is currently","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"serving as the outline for what I would like the algorithm to be. But","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as there isn’t something I know a lot about how to do correctly or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"really know the best way to achieve this.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Scribe grantees something to be visual selected. This might sound","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strange to some of you but if you think of your mouse or finger before","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you actually click this is sort of a way of selecting. Obviously those","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"examples are more complicated and I have ideas to work on them in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"future but best to start with the simplest example which I think is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the terminal and ASCII escape codes. Now It may be best to traverse","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the tree to the selected node and then “tile” out from there as I would","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"like to keep that element in the center of the screen give or take some","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"margin. Kinda to reflect similar behavior of vim letting you pad the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bottom of the text file.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The Next assumption is that text is to generally be centered in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"middle of the screen for now. Soon after I debug this algorithm I plan","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to surface apis for suggesting the text to be left or right, top or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bottom. But I think a nice default is for the text to be centered.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"I haven’t really thought how to handle clipping or word wrapping yet.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For now I think it’s best to just clip the text and allow the user to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pan around the graph. Which will mean I need to extend the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode","isActive":true},{"text":" type to allow deeper selections with in lines\/ words","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This will also be needed to visualize selecting charters of a word in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text editor which I am to build with this UI\/UX framework.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"I guess the last thing I should mentioned is text should consume the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"amount of space possible. Until the size of all nodes is know and we","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"know how much space to fill in around the information needing to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"displayed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Hopefully this helps other developers understanding what is going on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"here or at least future Zane. I have a somewhat working example of what","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"i’m trying to do in the ScribeModel repo. But I made different","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"assumptions about the AST there so the problem is just different enough","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"here but it is possible.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode\/drawVisible(_:_:)","role":"symbol"}}}